s, United Kingdom","Cardigan, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardigan, Cardiganshire, Wales","Llannerch Aeron, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Llannerch Aeron, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Hen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: from a short form of the personal name   Heinrich  .","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 田 based on its pronunciation of the Siyi Cantonese subdialect (also known as Sze Yup or Four Districts dialect including Taishanese) spoken in southern Guangdong, see   Tian   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Heinrich","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Kurt, Erwin, Helmut, Manfred, Otto, Dieter, Hans, Christl, Ewald, Gerd, Gerhard, Guenter.","German and Jewish (Ashkenazic): from the personal name <i>Heinrich</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>haim</i>, <i>heim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power’ (see also   Henry  ). In the Middle Ages this was the most popular of personal names in Germany."]}]},{"name":"Fychan","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Welsh: A Welsh name of great antiquity, from vyckan, little, small; i.e. small in stature. Compare the surname Bychan and the Armoric Le Bihan."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maelgwn Fychan ap Maelgwn Hen was born about 1185, in Wales, United Kingdom as the son of Maelgwn Hen ap Rhys. He had at least 2 sons and 2 daughters with Angharad ferch Llywelyn. He died in 1257, in Cardigan, Cardiganshire, Wales, at the age of 73."},"et":{"about 1185–1257":"umbes 1185–1257","1185–1257":"1185–1257","1210–1260":"1210–1260","1225–Female":"1225–Surnud","1232–1255":"1232–1255","–1230":"–1230","–1255":"–1255","1155–1230":"1155–1230","25 September 1255":"25. september 1255","1230":"1230","1185":"1185","1260":"1260","1225":"1225","1257":"1257","1255":"1255","1155":"1155","1232":"1232","1210":"1210","about 1225":"umbes 1225","about 1232":"umbes 1232","about 1185":"umbes 1185","Caemarvon, Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Caernarfonshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of Carmarthenshire, Wales":"Carmarthenshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Cardigan, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Cardigan, Cardiganshire, Wales","Llannerch Aeron, Cardiganshire, Wales":"Llannerch Aeron, Cardiganshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1185–1257":"noin 1185–1257","1185–1257":"1185–1257","1210–1260":"1210–1260","1225–Female":"1225–Kuollut","1232–1255":"1232–1255","–1230":"–1230","–1255":"–1255","1155–1230":"1155–1230","25 September 1255":"25. syyskuuta 1255","1230":"1230","1185":"1185","1260":"1260","1225":"1225","1257":"1257","1255":"1255","1155":"1155","1232":"1232","1210":"1210","about 1225":"noin 1225","about 1232":"no